tweet: U.S. farm policy promotes overproduction of dairy.  @wifarmersunion argues that pandemic aid made the problem worse by encouraging even more production. During the second half of 2020, U.S. dairy farmers added 93,000 cows, representing the fastest expansion in 22 years.
name: National Farmers Union
